text: I do find it funny that this movie can get away with saying it's "Based on true events" when the "true event" was literally a childhood experience the director had where someone mistakenly knocked on his families' door looking for someone who didn't live there. That's it. That's all that happened. Imagine if Texas Chainsaw Massacre wasn't based on Ed Gein's crimes (as loosely as TCM is already based around that) but rather, when Tobe Hooper came up with the idea to use a chainsaw as the main weapon. Like "Based on a true story". Oh, so what true story was the inspiration? "Oh, I was at the mall and I saw a chainsaw." That's it? "Well, yeah but then¬†I imagined what would have happened if I grabbed it and just started slashing people to pieces with it". So eseentially, 99% of the "truth" in the story is the director's imagination lol.
